column5: With this bonus of fall Im taking any opportunity to fish for these pesky green backed fish......While the boat get winterized tomm, happily I have many a friend to offer the boat for additional use....Seems like a window of weather this week so hopefully I ll go fish em in between all the steelhead of course Soon I ll miss these green backs and solely focus on the blue backs....            WHile the weather man has given some awsome fall windows, I still have managed more then a few outings on steelies.....some of the memorable fish from a pictorial aspect
Nice photos, fishing about as good as it gets.
Some real chunky bronze back aniceguy  Cool shots on the last 2 pics Thanks for sharing Leechman
Nice fish.  Can't complain about those smallies.
nice lookin fish....cool pictures you have of them steelies!
Herring are closed here Milo.LOL   Nice fish.
who hooks herring in simcoe man I gotta show you some new places to punch holes
Those steelie pics are awesome!  Love the river rock and leaves...nice touch there.
thanks Cliff, makes for a terrific reminder of the day
